\begin_layout Standard
The previous result suggests that conservatism in belief revision does not simply follow from people's cognitive difficulties when dealing with Bayes' rule. The higher likelihood to update correctly of those who approve the reform is robust evidence that ideology and political identity shape belief formation. Such directional motivated reasoning has been proposed by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
